Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: Well here is how i see it (sorry for people that have read this same thing many times already lol)

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: atomicDEX is a mobile version of the DEX. It is the first DEX via mobile so good for marketing.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: This will get people using it and trying it out.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: Next comes the desktop apps. This will allow more people to use it.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: Next comes the market maker functionality - this is where the magic comes into play.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content:
I will be able to hook up my app to the APIs of the exchange.

Say i want to trade KMD/BTC

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: KMD/BTC on binance is say 0.0002 as a example

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content:
On the desktop app i can set it to 5% spread, so i list my KMD (probably need some reserves within the wallet so it can complete in a reasonable time period) automatically for whatever the price i can buy it at binance + 5%.

So in this example i would set x amount of KMD at 0.00021

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: This rate is always changing obviously. But when someone buys my KMD on the DEX for 0.00021 it triggers a buy on the CEX at 0.0002

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: Thus making the 5%

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: Now if you are making 5% constantly risk free, i want to do the same. But how do i make sure my sells are done before yours? I set a lower margin, i do 4.9%

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: Ok now joe sees how easy i am making money, he sets it to 3%

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: This happens over and over until the market finds the lower % they are willing to take for this free money.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content:
Now the people that say well 1% is not worth the effort, will leave and maybe the price goes to 1.5% and they come back.

What it will do though, it make the DEX the most liquid exchange ever
